Parliament, Monday, 25 February 2019 – The Portfolio Committee on Communications will tomorrow, 26 February 2019, shortlist 24 candidates who will be interviewed to fill eight vacancies at the board of the South African Broadcasting Corporation (SABC). The 24 names will be published on Parliament’s website for public comment, for six days. Subsequent to that, the committee will conduct interviews over three days next week from 5 to 7 March 2019. The shortlisting will be conducted as follows: Date: 5-7 (Tuesday-Thursday) March 2019
	Time: 11:00
	Venue: Committee Room M201, Second Floor, Marks Building ISSUED BY PARLIAMENTARY COMMUNICATION SERVICES ON BEHALF OF THE CHAIRPERSON OF THE PORTFOLIO COMMITTEE ON COMMUNICATIONS, PROF HLEGIWE MKHIZE For media enquiries or interviews with the Chairperson, please contact media officer: Name: Mr Justice Molafo
	Tel: 021 403 8444
	Cell: 081 424 7481
	Email: jmolafo@parliament.gov.za The seat of Parliament is in Cape Town, but it could be moved by an Act of Parliament supported by a majority of the members of the National Assembly.Read more